    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear, then add it to a pot with a lid with the <strong>outer</strong> <strong>lemongrass layer[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low, then cover and cook for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>sticky lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
